  "texts": [
    "TAM and other similar models have been constructed to describe, understand and promote technology acceptance [152].",
    "The main factors highlighted and analyzed by such models include: Perceived usefulness, Perceived ease of use, Social influence/subjective norms, Perceived behavioral control/facilitating conditions.",
    "Each of these dimensions comprises several sub-dimensions.Despite their extensive use outside the health science and health care, the literature of using TAMs for health AI/ML acceptance is in its infancy.In a systematic review of randomized trials of ML interventions in health care, Plana et al. [153] sought to study the design, reporting standards, risk of bias, and inclusivity of RCTs for medical machine learning interventions.",
    "41 RCTs were identified with a median of 294 participants (range, 17-2488 participants).",
    "No trials adhered to all CONSORT-AI standards."
